@@ -0,0 +1,29 @@
+import cowsay
+import argparse
+
+parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(
+    prog="cowsay",
+    description="Make animals say things",
+)
+
+valid_animal = cowsay.char_names
+
+parser.add_argument(
+    "--animal",
+    choices=valid_animal,
+    default="cow",
+    help=" The animal to be saying things."
+)
+parser.add_argument(
+    "message", 
+    nargs="+", 
+    help="The message to say"
+)
+
+args = parser.parse_args()
+
+# to compose full msg
+message = " ".join(args.message)
+
+# Call selected cowsay func
+getattr(cowsay, args.animal)(message)

pull_request.body:
This PR contains the following updates: | Package | Change | Age | Confidence | |---|---|---|---| | [maunium.net/go/mautrix](https://redirect.github.com/mautrix/go) | `v0.24.2` -> `v0.25.0` | [![age](https://developer.mend.io/api/mc/badges/age/go/maunium.net%2fgo%2fmautrix/v0.25.0?slim=true)](https://docs.renovatebot.com/merge-confidence/) | [![confidence](https://developer.mend.io/api/mc/badges/confidence/go/maunium.net%2fgo%2fmautrix/v0.24.2/v0.25.0?slim=true)](https://docs.renovatebot.com/merge-confidence/) | --- ### Release Notes
mautrix/go (maunium.net/go/mautrix) ### [`v0.25.0`](https://redirect.github.com/mautrix/go/blob/HEAD/CHANGELOG.md#v0250-2025-08-16) [Compare Source](https://redirect.github.com/mautrix/go/compare/v0.24.2...v0.25.0) - Bumped minimum Go version to 1.24. - **Breaking change *(appservice,bridgev2,federation)*** Replaced gorilla/mux with standard library ServeMux. - *(client,bridgev2)* Added support for creator power in room v12. - *(client)* Added option to not set `User-Agent` header for improved Wasm compatibility. - *(bridgev2)* Added support for following tombstones. - *(bridgev2)* Added interface for getting arbitrary state event from Matrix. - *(bridgev2)* Added batching to disappearing message queue to ensure it doesn't use too many resources even if there are a large number of messages. - *(bridgev2/commands)* Added support for canceling QR login with `cancel` command. - *(client)* Added option to override HTTP client used for .well-known resolution. - *(crypto/backup)* Added method for encrypting key backup session without private keys. - *(event->id)* Moved room version type and constants to id package. - *(bridgev2)* Bots in DM portals will now be added to the functional members state event to hide them from the room name calculation. - *(bridgev2)* Changed message delete handling to ignore "delete for me" events if there are multiple Matrix users in the room. - *(format/htmlparser)* Changed text processing to collapse multiple spaces into one when outside `pre`/`code` tags. - *(format/htmlparser)* Removed link suffix in plaintext output when link text is only missing protocol part of href. - e.g. `example.com` will turn into `example.com` rather than `example.com (https://example.com)` - *(appservice)* Switched appservice websockets from gorilla/websocket to coder/websocket. - *(bridgev2/matrix)* Fixed encryption key sharing not ignoring ghosts properly. - *(crypto/attachments)* Fixed hash check when decrypting file streams. - *(crypto)* Removed unnecessary `AlreadyShared` error in `ShareGroupSession`. The function will now act as if it was successful instead.
--- ### Configuration 📅 **Schedule**: Branch creation - At any time (no schedule defined), Automerge - At any time (no schedule defined). 🚦 **Automerge**: Disabled by config. issue.title: performance audit on main page and about
issue.body:
feat: Refactor OfficeStructure component for performance and mobile layout

This commit introduces a series of refactorings to the `OfficeStructure` component to improve code organization, boost performance, and fix several mobile layout issues identified during a performance audit.

Key changes include:

- **Code Splitting**: The large `OfficeStructure.js` component has been broken down into three smaller, more focused components:
  - `departmentNav.js`: Handles the department selection sidebar.
  - `departmentDetails.js`: Manages the display of department-specific information (header, sub-departments, responsibilities).
  - `reportingStructure.js`: Renders the organizational chart.

- **Data Abstraction**: The `organizationStructure` data object has been moved to a dedicated file (`officeStructureData.js`), centralizing content and separating it from component logic. The deprecated crown emoji icon has also been removed as requested.

- **Mobile Layout Fixes**:
  - The main container cards are now properly centered on mobile viewports, preventing them from flushing against the right border.
  - The sub-departments and key responsibilities containers now have equal spacing on both sides for improved visual appeal.
  - The reporting structure cards have been enhanced with a single-column layout on smaller screens to prevent text overflow and improve readability.
  - The `next/image` component syntax was updated to use modern props, replacing the deprecated `objectFit` prop with the `style` attribute to prevent warnings and ensure optimal image rendering performance.

These changes lead to a cleaner, more maintainable codebase and a significantly better user experience on mobile devices.

issue.title: Setup CI/CD to auto-update nix-config when VSCode settings change
issue.body:
## 概要
このリポジトリの設定ファイルが更新されたときに、自動的に https://github.com/naitokosuke/nix-config のflakeを更新するCI/CDを設定する。

## 対象ファイル
- `.vscode/**`
- `keybinding.jsonc`

## 実装内容
1. GitHub Actionsワークフローの作成
   - mainブランチへのpush時に起動
   - 対象ファイルの変更を検知
   - nix-configリポジトリでflake updateを実行
   - 自動でPRを作成

## 必要な設定
- GitHub Personal Access Token (PAT) を `GITHUB_TOKEN` として設定
  - nix-configリポジトリへの書き込み権限が必要

## ワークフローファイル
`.github/workflows/update-nix-config.yml` を作成済み

pull_request.title: feat: implement Cookie Consent Banner with comprehensive testing
pull_request.body:
## 概要

実装計画8.2に基づき、TDD（Test-Driven Development）でCookieConsentBannerコンポーネントを実装しました。

## 主な変更内容

### 新機能
- **CookieConsentBanner**: プライバシー設定管理のためのユーザー同意バナー
- **App.tsx統合**: メインアプリケーションへのバナー表示

### アーキテクチャ改善
- **PrivacyManager初回訪問時ロジック**: `null`による自然な初期状態管理
- **型安全性向上**: TypeScript best practicesに基づく改善
- **エラーハンドリング強化**: カテゴライズされた例外処理

### コード品質
- **包括的テスト**: 22のテストケース（境界値・統合・アクセシビリティ・エラーハンドリング）
- **DRY/KISS原則**: レスポンシブ設定統合・共通イベントハンドラー・テストヘルパー
- **React最適化**: useEffect依存配列最適化・メモ化パターン

## 技術詳細

### TDD実装サイクル
1. **Red**: 失敗するテストを先に作成
2. **Green**: 最小限の実装でテストを通す  
3. **Refactor**: UI/UX・パフォーマンス・保守性を向上

### 重要な修正
- **初回訪問時の改善**: 期限切れタイムスタンプの代わりに`null`による自然な状態管理
- **型安全性**: 危険な型アサーション（`as any`）を全て除去
- **パフォーマンス**: useEffect無限ループリスクの解決

### 品質保証
- **コードレビュー**: React・TypeScript・DRY/KISS・QA各専門エージェントによる検証
- **品質チェック**: ESLint・TypeScript・テスト実行の完全クリア
- **アクセシビリティ**: ARIA属性・キーボードナビゲーション対応

## テスト範囲

```
✓ 基本表示・非表示ロジック
✓ ユーザー操作（同意・拒否）
✓ PrivacyManager統合
✓ LocalStorage例外処理
✓ レスポンシブ境界値
✓ キーボードアクセシビリティ
✓ 初期化エラーハンドリング
```

## 変更ファイル

- `src/components/CookieConsentBanner.tsx` - メインコンポーネント
- `src/components/CookieConsentBanner.test.tsx` - 包括的テストスイート
- `src/services/privacyManager.ts` - 初回訪問時ロジック改善
- `src/utils/privacyUtils.ts` - ドキュメント更新
- `src/App.tsx` - バナー統合
- テスト修正: `usePrivacySettings.test.ts`, `NurseryCard.test.tsx`

## 破壊的変更

なし（既存APIは完全に後方互換）

## 次のステップ

実装計画の残りタスク（8.3以降）への準備が完了しました。
